features.name: S1 acts as an RNA chaperone to unfold structured mRNA on the ribosome but is not essential for mRNAs with strong SDs and little 5'-UTR structure, thus it may help fine-tune which mRNAs that are translated. Unwinds dsRNA by binding to transiently formed ssRNA regions

Form_Nir_trans Involved in the bidirectional transport of formate

Fer4_12,Radical_SAM under anaerobic conditions by generation of an organic free radical, using S- adenosylmethionine and reduced flavodoxin as cosubstrates to produce 5'-deoxy-adenosine
Fer4_11,Fer4_3,Fer4_4 Anaerobic dimethyl sulfoxide reductase chain B

Seryl_tRNA_N,tRNA-synt_2b Catalyzes the attachment of serine to tRNA(Ser). Is also able to aminoacylate tRNA(Sec) with serine, to form the misacylated tRNA L-seryl-tRNA(Sec), which will be further converted into selenocysteinyl-tRNA(Sec)
AAA,AAA_assoc_2,MgsA_C,RuvB_N DNA-dependent ATPase that plays important roles in cellular responses to stalled DNA replication processes

LolA Participates in the translocation of lipoproteins from the inner membrane to the outer membrane. Only forms a complex with a lipoprotein if the residue after the N-terminal Cys is not an aspartate (The Asp acts as a targeting signal to indicate that the lipoprotein should stay in the inner membrane)
FtsK_4TM,FtsK_SpoIIIE,Ftsk_gamma COG1674 DNA segregation ATPase FtsK SpoIIIE and related proteins
AsnC_trans_reg,HTH_24 lrp mediates this effect for at least some of these operons. For example it is regulator of the branched-chain amino acid transport genes
Pyr_redox_2 Belongs to the class-II pyridine nucleotide-disulfide oxidoreductase family

Leu_Phe_trans Functions in the N-end rule pathway of protein degradation where it conjugates Leu, Phe and, less efficiently, Met from aminoacyl-tRNAs to the N-termini of proteins containing an N-terminal arginine or lysine

eIF-1a One of the essential components for the initiation of protein synthesis. Stabilizes the binding of IF-2 and IF-3 on the 30S subunit to which N-formylmethionyl-tRNA(fMet) subsequently binds. Helps modulate mRNA selection, yielding the 30S pre- initiation complex (PIC). Upon addition of the 50S ribosomal subunit IF-1, IF-2 and IF-3 are released leaving the mature 70S translation initation complex

AAA,AAA_2,ClpB_D2-small,Clp_N ATP-dependent specificity component of the ClpAP protease. It directs the protease to specific substrates. It has unfoldase activity. The primary function of the ClpA-ClpP complex appears to be the degradation of unfolded or abnormal proteins
ClpS Involved in the modulation of the specificity of the ClpAP-mediated ATP-dependent protein degradation

CSD Inhibits DNA replication at both initiation and elongation steps, most probably by binding to the opened, single- stranded regions at replication forks. Plays a regulatory role in chromosomal replication in nutrient-depleted cells

ABC_tran,FtsX,MacB_PCD Part of the tripartite efflux system MacAB-TolC. MacB is a non-canonical ABC transporter that contains transmembrane domains (TMD), which form a pore in the inner membrane, and an ATP-binding domain (NBD), which is responsible for energy generation

HlyD_D23 Part of the tripartite efflux system MacAB-TolC. MacA stimulates the ATPase activity of MacB by promoting the closed ATP-bound state of MacB, increases the capacity of MacB to bind macrolides such as erythromycin, and provides a physical link between MacB and TolC
DUF535 cellular response to DNA damage stimulus
DUF2813 DNA synthesis involved in DNA repair

MIP Channel that permits osmotically driven movement of water in both directions. It is involved in the osmoregulation and in the maintenance of cell turgor during volume expansion in rapidly growing cells. It mediates rapid entry or exit of water in response to abrupt changes in osmolarity
Lys_export L-lysine efflux transmembrane transporter activity
Prismane Catalyzes the reduction of hydroxylamine to form NH(3) and H(2)O
TPP_enzyme_C,TPP_enzyme_M,TPP_enzyme_N Belongs to the TPP enzyme family
Beta_elim_lyase Catalyzes the cleavage of L-allo-threonine and L- threonine to glycine and acetaldehyde. L-threo-phenylserine and L- erythro-phenylserine are also good substrates
YbjQ_1 Belongs to the UPF0145 family
ABC_tran Part of the ABC transporter complex ArtPIQMJ involved in arginine transport. Probably responsible for energy coupling to the transport system
SBP_bac_3 Belongs to the bacterial solute-binding protein 3 family
BPD_transp_1 Part of the ABC transporter complex ArtPIQMJ involved in arginine transport. Probably responsible for the translocation of the substrate across the membrane
